{{Infobox non-profit | name = Gavi, the Vaccine Alliance | image = | caption = | type = Public–Private Partnership | location = [[Geneva]], Switzerland | key_people = [[Seth Berkley]], [[Dagfinn Høybråten]] | status = Active | founded_date = {{Start date and age|2000}} | mission = Saving children’s lives and protecting people’s health by increasing access to immunisation in poor countries | foci = Vaccines against: human diseases | homepage = [http://www.gavi.org/ www.gavi.org] | website = {{URL|www.gavi.org}} }}
'''Gavi, the Vaccine Alliance''' ('''Gavi''' for short; previously the '''GAVI Alliance''',<ref name="2014_ravelo">{{cite web |url=https://www.devex.com/news/the-evolution-of-global-health-s-best-kept-secret-84782 |publisher=Devex |title=The evolution of global health's 'best-kept secret' |first=Jenny Lei |last=Ravelo |date=November 10, 2014 |accessdate=January 25, 2017}}</ref> and before that the '''Global Alliance for Vaccines and Immunization''')<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gavi.org/library/news/press-releases/2006/brazil-announces-support-for-global-immunisation-and-iffim/ |title=Brazil announces support for global immunisation and IFFIm |publisher=Gavi |date=March 9, 2006 |accessdate=January 25, 2017 |quote=The new funds will support the work of the GAVI Alliance (formerly the Global Alliance for Vaccines and Immunization)}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.healthandcommunications.com/blog/2014/10/28/gavi-a-new-brand |publisher=Health and Communications |title=Gavi: A New Brand |accessdate=January 25, 2017 |first=Rick |last=Lesaar |date=November 3, 2014 |quote=With a lead capital ''G'' and lower case ''avi'', the Alliance's name is no longer an acronym. Originally it was the ''Global Alliance for Vaccines and Immunisations'', then most recently the ''GAVI Alliance'', and now ''Gavi, the Vaccine Alliance''.}}</ref> is a [[Public–private partnership|public–private]] global health partnership committed to increasing access to immunisation in poor countries.<ref>{{cite web|last=Boseley |first=Sarah |url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/sarah-boseley-global-health/2011/nov/17/vaccines-pharmaceuticals-industry |title=Green light from Gavi for cervical cancer vaccine |publisher=Guardian |date=2011-11-17 |accessdate=2014-04-29}}</ref>
Gavi brings together developing country and donor governments, the [[World Health Organization]], [[UNICEF]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unicef.org/supply/index_gavi.html |title=Supplies and Logistics - GAVI |publisher=UNICEF |date=2007-04-09 |accessdate=2013-01-27}}</ref> the [[World Bank]], the vaccine industry in both industrialised and developing countries, research and technical agencies, civil society, the [[Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation]] and other private philanthropists.
==History== [[File:Bill Gates, speaking at the UK-hosted GAVI immunisation Alliance pledging event.jpg|thumb|[[Bill Gates]], speaking at the UK-hosted Gavi pledging event in June 2011]]
Gavi was created in 2000 as a successor to the [[Children's Vaccine Initiative]], which had been launched in 1990.<ref>{{cite web|title=Gavi - About|url=http://www.gavi.org/about/|website=gavi.org|accessdate=24 October 2017}}</ref>
Dr. Seth Berkley has been the CEO of GAVI since 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gavi.org/library/news/press-releases/2011/dr-seth-berkley-appointed-as-gavi-alliance-chief-executive-officer/|title=Dr Seth Berkley appointed as GAVI Alliance Chief Executive Officer|author=|date=|website=www.gavi.org|accessdate=14 April 2018}}</ref>
The [[Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation]] has donated $1.5 billion to the alliance as of January 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gatesfoundation.org/about/Pages/foundation-fact-sheet.aspx |title=Foundation Fact Sheet – Bill & Melinda Gates Foundation |publisher=Gatesfoundation.org |date= |accessdate=2013-01-27}}</ref>
In August 2014, Gavi changed its name from "GAVI Alliance" and introduced a new logo. Both changes were revealed in August;<ref name="2014_ravelo" /> it had by then acquired the gavi.org [[domain name]] and changed its primary domain from gavialliance.org to gavi.org.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140101000000*/http://www.gavi.org/ |title=Internet Archive Wayback Machine |accessdate=January 25, 2017 |publisher=Internet Archive}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gavi.org/library/news/press-releases/year/2014/ |title=Press releases, 2014 |publisher=Gavi |accessdate=January 25, 2017}}</ref>
